2001-12-29 19:26 UTC+0100 Ron Pinkas <ron@ronpinkas.com>
  * xharbour/include/hbfast.h
  * xharbour/source/vm/fastitem.c
    + void hb_itemPushForward( PHB_ITEM pItem );

  * xharbour/source/vm/estack.c
  * xharbour/source/vm/itemapi.c
  * xharbour/source/vm/hvm.c
    ! Optimized many hb_vmPush() to new hb_itemPushForward()
    ! Optimized many hb_itemCopy() to new hb_itemForwardValue()

  /*
     After this 2nd optimization installment, xHarbour is now about 10-15% faster than Harbour.
     For example on my 1Ghz Notebook, hbtest.exe (output directed to file) takes 0.85 Second,
     as oppose to Harbour's 0.97 Second.

     All tests run fine.
  */

